# Alembic Migrations

## One-Time Production Stamp (CRITICAL)

**Before the first deploy** with this Alembic setup, on the **server** (where the production DB lives):

```bash
cd /path/to/al-amanah
docker compose run --rm backend alembic stamp head
```

Then deploy (e.g. `./redeploy.sh`). This stamps the existing DB so `upgrade head` does nothing on startup and avoids "table already exists" errors.

## Future Schema Changes

1. Edit models in `backend/app/models/`
2. `cd backend && alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description"`
3. Review the migration in `alembic/versions/`
4. `alembic upgrade head` locally
5. Commit the migration file, deploy; `init_db()` runs `upgrade head` on startup
